caption: I called them to order. Before I order I ask one of the guy who take my call how do you cook chicken tikka masala. I just  wanna know do they grill chicken first or just put normal chicken in curry. And this guy  told me everyone know how the chicken tikka cooked. If someone try Indian food first time then what they will do .. they don’t know how to take care of a customer. Just one word to explain then is Disgusting . I will never call them for food . Be careful guys from those guy .
I prefer this place a lot. there is a great mood. The meals are splendid. the service is dynamic and the team is polite. The price is fair. I definitely recommend.
Anarkali’s food is delicious. My favorites are the mango chicken and the saag aloo. The chicken tikka masala is also delicious, as is the naan. The only thing I don’t recommend is the gulab jamun.
Delicious as always. My go to Indian spot!

I enjoy Indian Cuisine, but every Kitchen makes its own  specialties & flavors.  I found that Anarkali takes special care when preparing their dishes.  I enjoy dishes such as Mango Chicken,  Samosas, fish or vegetable dishes!  The flavors & authenticity I've become acustomed to long ago, are esplendidly re-created at Anarkali, and they do not shay away from suggestions! Thanks, Anarkaly!
They lied and stole from me. I reordered the special and an additional plate. I did not get my navrata korma or the samosa. I am finished with them after several orders.

I take my family to this place often! This is my favorite place to grab a bite.  I go there at least once a month. The cooking is excellent, the crew is polite and the payment is good. I like eating in this restaurant to have a tasty lunch.

I celebrated my birthday yesterday in this gorgeous place. I am glad to say that it was a delightful evening and the place was unquestionably one of the reasons for this strong evening. The stuff  cooperated in a splendid manner, the cooking was extremely good and my friends were so  thrilled. We shall surely come back again for more events. Thank you very much.
OK

The most awful service I've ever experienced. It all started after I got a promotional coupon for dinning in this restaurant.  The first time I came there I was told that this coupon is not valid for take away (wtf!?, but ok), though at that time there was no customer because of the late hour, the guy said that we can sit and eat in there.  So I decided to give them a second try and actually dine in there with my family. But when we arrived there for the second time we were informed that it's unexpectedly closed and no explanation why. On top of that when asked they couldn't tell what their actual working hours are, either because of utter ignorance and incompetence or simply lack of English 😅  So, future customer, beware of this restaurant. As it has no fixed working hours and no competent workers which can give you meaningful answers and arguments!
Always most enjoyable dinners.
Great food, but terrible service. Forgot and messed up my order several times and phone attendant was very rude. Made me not wanna order from them ever again.
Food was undercooked and nothing like the pictures!!! Also, was missing one thing that I ordered and paid extra for!
Good food reasonably priced
Excellent Indian cuisine and service. Not many people know how terrific this spot is. Easy parking, too. Could use a few plants and pictures...lots of natural light.

The delivery from this place is good. But in house service experience is the worst. The server just doesn’t seem interested in his job. The chicken served to us was not tender, felt like it was reheated in the microwave and served. The chef didn’t seem interested either just like the servers.  In all honesty, I would not suggest in house dining to anyone unless they’re in a mood for a completely disastrous experience.
Excellent undiscovered restaurant. First rate food and reasonable prices. I really like Indian food and this is my restaurant of choice
I've never been here but I order alot from them for delivery.  Always timely,  tasty and affordable.
Meh. Food was plentiful and cheap, but poorly executed.
This is easily the best Indian food I've had. Everything I've eaten here has simply blown my mind.
Nothing to say other than we had some really fantastic Indian food here. Will visit again. Highly recommended!! ☺
Great food good atmosphere cheap price...waiter could of smile other than that well recommend
Very rude phone attended. Ordered a delivery. Guy said he did not have time to take care of my order. Will never order from them again .
By far this is my favorite Indian food spot in Brooklyn. Very tasty with good portions plus they always treat me nice.
The lamb biryani  was delicious plus the service was great! Definitely going back.
Great food and service. Highly recommended.

So I ordered from them on my Seamless app a few times and the food is really delicious. So I decided to go by their restraunt and see what it looks like on the inside. It's a romantic dimly lit VERY CLEAN restraunt, I would love to come here on a date night. They even have a 50% of lunch special when you dine in! Gotta come here for lunch and pig out! Lol The food is so good you'll keep stuffing your face even after you're full because you don't want to waste a bite. The servings are generous in comparison to other places that serve similar menu items. Give it a chance, I don't think you'll be disappointed 1/5/2019

Ordered naan and butter chicken from them. I had butter chicken from so many places now. The sauce was too runny and not creamy. The chicken was weird teasting. The naan was okay. Do not recommend it. I went around dinner time and the restaurant was empty. U can imagine.

I ordered food two hours ago and am still waiting. When I ordered the man taking my order said my address was very far for such a small order. Still he took my credit card info and accepted the order. I just called to see where my food was and he said “you are too far”. He then said he thinks the delivery guy is on his way but has no idea when he will arrive! This is total BS!!!
I like snacks from this restuarant
i love to eat

There is a significant difference between the takeout and the eat-in food. Eat-in always seems much better. We won't order take out from here anymore. They recently got their health grade up to an A from a B, so maybe its better now. The ambiance is .... zero. If they made it feel like a little more of a special experience to eat there more people would probably come. Play music or something! Hang pictures on the walls!
Cheap good food during lunch hour. In House only.

If I can give zero stars, I would. I ordered chicken tikka masala and garlic naan bread. Having ordered it countless times from other restaurants, I was expecting a thick delicious creamy sauce. Instead, I got a watery red sauce with UNDERCOOKED MEAT. After having to chew the meat way too many times, I realized once I cut into another cube of meat that was undercooked. Things happen right? I gave the restaurant a call where the man I spoke with informed me that is the way the dish is served. I stressed the meat was undercooked and he was welcome to come and get it for inspection. He once again stated that's the way it is served. Okay, so this restaurant serves undercooked meat by its own admission. What's worst? He at no point offered to make it right at all. Informing the general public so we can protect ourselves from food poisoning or worst. Makes me wonder what else could be going on in there. I will reach out to the health department. For now, order somewhere safe.
Food was excellent. The server was rude.

Poor service,  we waited 5 minutes for someone to take our order. We were the only ones inside so I thought we would be greeted friendly.  To the contrary.  I've tasted better Indian food. First and last visit.
Not a good quality food. Won't recommend.

Too much oil in our 3 birianys even though we asked to add less oil. Prices are higher according to the serving size. Also, we wondered if their air conditioner was working enough. Outside was around 87°F and we didn't feel any cool temperature. It was warm inside. We asked about their air conditioner and the stuff replied with rude attitude!
Never had complaints about their food. The restraunt itself is often empty, I assume most do take out. They have a good dine in special for lunch.

The chef is extremely rude and NASTY  !! I was dining there , and I literally saw him picking his nose while sitting across the table.  They also increased the price but did not update their menu. So look for hidden charges.
Good local restaurant
Indian food is a part of who I am. This place gets it right. EVERYTHING is good. The waiter was incredibly nice and even gave us a free dessert.

I have ordered here once before and had no complaints, but this time I ordered and the food was inedible. The chicken tikka masala I ordered was flavorless and watery. The chicken was tough and hard to chew. I have ordered this same thing before and it was nothing like this, so they must have made a mistake. On top of this there were multiple thick black hairs strewn about the food. They also added food that I didnt order and I was forced to pay for it. When I called them to let them know, the person on the phone yelled at me and called me a liar and accused me of “placing the hairs there myself” and tried telling me that I DID order the extra food. I asked for different food or a refund and the guy hung up on me. I’m still in shock and cannot believe the way he spoke to me. There are so many other great places to order from in this neighborhood-whatever you do, don’t pick this one.

The best Indian meal I have had in Brooklyn. The chicken tikka masala was tender and rich. The vegetable sambusa was also very good and came with a variety of unique dipping sauces. A very cozy environment, highly recommend!
Perfect neighborhood spot with delicious food.  Despite it being a busy night, our host was so friendly and attentive. Highly recommend!

We used to order twice weekly, not any more.. Potatoes not cooked well, cauliflower was very hard and no matter we ask nicely please make the food not too spicey and cook the food well, they never listen..time for a change!
expensive food is not great
Food was great. Didn't take a long time.
Good food.
Best Indian food I have had in our area

This is our neighborhood's favorite restaurant. We come here about twice a month. We love all the vegetarian dishes they have there. Super flavorful and generous. We are known by the staff and they have been very friendly towards us. Best feature are the special deals: the 50% in-house lunch discount and the lunch boxes to go!

I happened to notice this restaurant as I was on my way to work. I like Indian food so I decided to give it a try. It was a very nice experience overall. I ordered the seafood curry, asking that it be made as least spicy as possible, and a mango lassi. The food took a little while to come out, even though there was only one other person in the establishment, but it was worth the wait. The curry was delicious & just the right size. The mango lassi was served in a tall glass & was also very tasty. Street parking can get a bit tricky here, but the food & service make this one restaurant that I recommend.
Best Indian food
Ok Indian food experience. It was ok portions and the food was only ok... Just a little taken aback when we say the B grade in the window.

I got to admit that living close to Richmond Hill (Queens) excellent indian restaurants spoiled me a bit...nevertheless I did not expect the food to be so bland, completeley lacking seasoning and salt. Tandoori meats were overkooked beyond edible.
I ordered an Anarkali deal, the food arrived WITHOUT rice. I called the number and they said the delivery guy can't come back to bring the missing rice. Worst experience ever.
Very tasty indian food with a great portion. And the restaurant is very quiet beautiful one. Definitely go again

I've never eaten at the restaurant, but it's close to my apartment and has a fantastic seamless deal. great service, and the one time they were delayed, I called and the apologized profusely -- I had my food just a few minutes later. a solid staple in our house on busy weeknights when there's no time to cook.  EDIT: dropped to 1 star because they delivered a live roach to my apartment. I will NEVER order from them again.
Great food and super friendly, fast service.
Authentic Indian cuisine! Great food ,fast delivery!
Such a worst customer service.

I ordered food from Anarkali yesterday and spent around $40 for the food which was no problem,  I was looking forward to the food so badly, I was really hungry.  The  much awaited food arrived finally.  I took my first bite and was like ewwwww, the food tasted so bad.  I ordered spinach and cauliflower/potato (i am a vegetarian) spinach tasted like it was boiled and then they sauteed some onions and just threw boiled spinach in it...tasted awful, same thing for cauliflower/potatoes, tasted boiled and sauteed in heavily loaded curry powder and onions, ewwwww... unbelievable, horrible tasting food.  What a waste of money.  I will never order from this place again...I wish I could give ZERO stars but didn't have a choice. I guess people who gave anything above 1 star don't know what Indian food is supposed to taste like that's why they did that.
Food was delicious and delivery was very fast .we definitely order again
Went here and the food is great its very calm and an overall nice restaurant
Fast delivery service! Food was delicious and Naan was fluffy..will definitely order from them again!

The food was great I ordered take out. First off they were very polite on the phone, speedy service, food delivered was hot, fresh, and my order was correct. Not only did the taste hit my palate well it also sat well on my stomach which not many Indian food restaurants do that for me. They also gave a complimentary desert which was awesome. I would order again and recommend this place to anyone in my area or in the area in which they deliver. Great job guys!
Great food

I had food from this restaurant before and food was average but service is horrible. Multiple times they forget to put utensils. Tonight I ordered from them at 7:30pm on seamless and because they didn't deliver yet, I called them at 9:15pm and was told super busy tonight and would take half an hour. After half an hour I called back and all I got were busy signal. Food was never delivered. I called seamless to get a refund but now stuck with no food for the night.  So angry. Will never order from this place again.
Great food. Best Indian food in the neighborhood and one of the best in Brooklyn.
